Ingredients
* 1 large eggplant (peeled and chopped*)
* 4 large tomatoes (peeled, seeded and chopped)
* 3 cloves of garlic (finely chopped or pressed)
* 1/3 cup chopped fresh cilantro and parsley (mixed)
* 1 tablespoon paprika
* 1 tablespoon cumin
* 1 1/2 teaspoons salt
* 1/8 teaspoon cayenne pepper (optional)
* 1/4 cup olive oil
* 1/3 cup water
* Small wedge of lemon (optional)

To Make the Zaalouk:
* Mix all ingredients in a large, deep skillet or pot. Cover and simmer over medium to medium-high heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Adjust the heat if necessary to avoid burning the zaalouk. Use a spoon or potato masher to crush and blend the tomatoes and eggplant. If you like, a small wedge of lemon can be added to the pan at this time. Continue simmering, uncovered, for 10 minutes or until the liquids are reduced and the zaalouk can be stirred into a heap in the center of the pan.

Purple blueberry cookies! YUM by @feelgoodfoodie 

INGREDIENTS
1 cup all-purpose flour
½ teaspoon baking powder
⅛ teaspoon salt
⅓ cup softened butter
⅓ cup granulated sugar
⅓ cup frozen blueberries
⅓ cup white chocolate chips

—> Bake at 400°F 10-13 minutes

node.text:
5 minute salted caramel sauce via @wholesomehedonista (dairy-free)

1/4 cup canned full fat coconut milk (thick white part on top of can I use Thai kitchen brand)
1/4 cup + 1 tbsp coconut sugar
Generous pinch salt

Mix ingredients together in a tall glass or bowl until smooth. Microwave about 1-2 mins (microwaves can vary). It’ll thicken as it cools. Perfect for apples or ice cream hope you enjoy! 😊 

#Eatwaybetter #healthyswaps #recipes #cheflife #cookingvideo #foody #foodnetwork #plantbasedcooking #foodshare #foodismedicine #eatbetter

node.text:
YUM Healthy air fryer 100 calorie dessert (via @wholesomehedonista 

Repost: “Slice a peach in half, remove pit. Spray flesh side with a little avocado or coconut oil spray. Air fry flesh side down for about 8-10 minutes at 350. If desired, flip peach over and cook flesh side up for 3-5 more minutes to brown the top. In the meantime lightly toast and finely chop some pistachios. Plate peach and top with a little coconut whipped cream, a generous amount of cinnamon (I was being skimpy in the video more tastes better), chopped pistachios and a drizzle of agave or honey if not vegan. Enjoy ❤️”
